article.headline: (2) MISSOURI ST 60, (3) HOUSTON 59
article.story:
SPRINGFIELD, Missouri (Ticker) -- Not enjoying much success 
from 3-point range, Missouri State decided to go for three the
old-fashioned way.

Nathan Bilyeu converted a three-point play with 2.3 seconds
remaining to lift the second-seeded Bears to a 60-59 victory
over No. 3 Houston in the second round of the National
Invitation Tournament.

With Missouri State trailing, 59-57, in the waning seconds,
Bilyeu made a jumper as he was fouled by Jahmar Thorpe.  Bilyeu
made the free throw to cap a 12-point effort as the Bears (22-8)
advanced to the quarterfinals for a matchup with Louisville.

On its final possession, Houston (21-10) had its full-court pass
intercepted.

Kellen Easley collected 14 points and 11 rebounds and Shane
Laurie added nine points for Missouri State, which made just
3-of-14 attempts from the arc and committed 24 turnovers.

The Cougars were led by Lanny Smith, who made five 3-pointers en
route to 21 points.  Ramon Dyer added 16 points for Houston,
whcih shot only 32 percent (20-of-62) and was outrebounded,
45-24.
